SENATE RESOLUTION 344
By Seal
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend SafeSpace on the
occasion of its fiftieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pay tribute to
those exemplary institutions that work with purpose and conviction to protect the well-being of
Tennessee's citizens and strengthen their communities; and
WHEREAS, SafeSpace is one such outstanding organization, which is marking fifty
years of dedicated service assisting victims of domestic violence and their children in East
Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, SafeSpace began in 1976 as a grassroots effort when a network of women
in the mountainous Appalachian region of East Tennessee opened their homes to shelter
victims of domestic violence and their children, demonstrating compassion and courage in
addressing a critical need within their communities; and
WHEREAS, this early effort soon evolved into the Cosby Coalition Against Domestic
Violence, which organized formally in 1979 and incorporated as a nonprofit charitable
organization in 1981, thereby establishing a structured and sustainable response to domestic
violence in the region; and
WHEREAS, in 1983, SafeSpace secured office space in the City Hall of Newport and
hired its first staff members, marking an important step toward expanding services to victims in
need; and
WHEREAS, on June 25, 1985, the organization opened its first shelter, providing refuge
and safety to women and children fleeing abusive situations, and the shelter has remained an
essential resource for victims of domestic violence ever since; and
SR0344
