WHEREAS, SafeSpace has been an integral part of the movement to end domestic
violence in Tennessee and was among the founding members of the Tennessee Coalition
Against Domestic and Sexual Violence; and
WHEREAS, the organization also played a historic role in securing the first rural order of
protection in the State of Tennessee and has since become widely regarded as a model for
rural shelter services; and
WHEREAS, through its emergency shelter, crisis intervention services, counseling, court
advocacy, resource referrals, and educational outreach, SafeSpace has provided critical
support to countless individuals and families seeking safety and stability; and
WHEREAS, guided by its mission to end domestic violence by supporting and
empowering victims while educating the community, SafeSpace continues to work tirelessly to
promote awareness, prevention, and healing for those affected by abuse; and
WHEREAS, the continued success of SafeSpace is due, in large measure, to the
dedication and compassion of its staff, volunteers, and supporters, whose tireless efforts have
provided safety, advocacy, and hope to individuals and families in need; and
WHEREAS, through its many programs and services, SafeSpace has played a vital role
in promoting safety, stability, and healing for victims of domestic violence while strengthening
families and communities throughout the region; and
WHEREAS, for fifty years, the dedicated staff, volunteers, and supporters of SafeSpace
have demonstrated compassion, perseverance, and a steadfast commitment to protecting
vulnerable individuals and strengthening the communities they serve; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we honor and commend
SafeSpace upon the occasion of its fiftieth anniversary and extend our appreciation to its
- 2 - 015519

leadership, staff, volunteers, and supporters for their many years of dedicated service to victims
of domestic violence and their families.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
